Task:
Suppose a family has 2 children, one of which is a boy. What is the probability that both children are boys?

Explination:

==> first children is boy and second is boy (BB)
    first children is boy and second is girl (BG)
    first children is girl and second is girl (GG)
    
==> probability that both children are boys 
    1(BB)/3(BB,BG,GG)
    
==> Answer = 1/3

